{
  "texts": [
    "This leads to a personalized learning experience that is tailored to learners' specific prior knowledge, competence levels, and attitudes.",
    "To foster SRL in students, strategic prompting can be employed to generate feedback in the form of cognitively activating instructions as suggested by Hofer and colleagues (Hofer et al., 1175).",
    "For instance, by posing questions about students' understanding, we can generate metacognitive scaffolds that encourage monitoring and self-reflection, as these content-specific scaffolds play a pivotal role in enhancing comprehension.",
    "Additionally, motivational prompts can be used to inspire and motivate students, thereby cultivating a conducive learning environment.",
    "Second, in addition to personalizing the different levels of formative feedback, LLMs allow verbal interaction and stimulate learners to ask questions when they lack understanding or competencies."
  ]
}